item.description:
arXiv:2606.11593v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: Using a dataset of 7.33 fb$^{-1}$ of $e^+ e^-$ annihilation data collected with the BESIII detector at center-of-mass energies from 4.128 to 4.226 GeV, we report an updated measurement of the branching fraction of $D_s^+ 	o 	au^+ 
u_{	au}$ via four $	au^+$ decay modes: $	au^+ 	o e^+ 
u_e  ar{
u}_{	au}$, $\mu^+ 
u_{\mu}  ar{
u}_{	au}$, $\pi^+ ar{
u}_{	au}$, and $\pi^+ \pi^{0}  ar{
u}_{	au}$. The branching fraction is determined to be $\mathcal{B}({D_s^+ 	o 	au^+ 
u_{	au}}) = (5.37 \pm 0.08_{m stat} \pm 0.06_{m syst})$ %. The product of the modulus of the Cabibbo-Kobayashi-Maskawa matrix element $|V_{cs}|$ and the $D_s^+$ decay constant $f_{D_s^+}$ is measured to be $f_{D_s^+} |V_{cs}| = (248.2 \pm 1.9_{m stat} \pm 1.4_{m syst} \pm 0.6_{m input} \pm 0.8_{m EM})$ MeV. Both the branching fraction and the product $f_{D_s^+} |V_{cs}|$ are the most precise results yet obtained. Then, taking $f_{D_s^+}$ from lattice quantum chromodynamics calculations results in $|V_{cs}| = 0.993 \pm 0.008_{m stat} \pm 0.006_{m syst} \pm 0.003_{m input} \pm 0.003_{m EM}$. Conversely, one finds $f_{D_s^+} = (255.0 \pm 1.9_{m stat} \pm 1.4_{m syst} \pm 0.6_{m input} \pm 0.8_{m EM})$ MeV when taking $|V_{cs}|$ from the CKMfitter group as an input. Combining with the world average value of $D_s^+ 	o \mu^+ 
u_{\mu}$, the ratio of the branching fractions between $D_s^+ 	o 	au^+ 
u_{	au}$ and $D_s^+ 	o \mu^+ 
u_{\mu}$ is estimated to be $10.04 \pm 0.29$, which is consistent with the Standard Model prediction of lepton flavor universality.
